{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2014}} '''Henry Neville Hutchinson''' {{postnominals|country=GBR|sep=,|FGS|FRGS|FZS}} (1856, [[Chester]] – 1927) was an Anglican clergyman and, during the 1890s, a leading writer of popular books on geology, [[palaeontology]], [[evolution]] and [[anthropology]].<ref>{{cite book|editor=Lightman, Bernard V.|editorlink=Bernard Lightman|editor2=Zon, Bennett|chapter=Henry Neville Hutchinson|title=Evolution and Victorian Culture|page=305|year=2014|publisher=Cambridge U. Press|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Z_6QAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA305}}</ref><ref name="Who">{{cite magazine|title=Hutchinson, Rev. H. N.|magazine=Who's Who|year=1907|volume= 59|pages=901–902|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=yEcuAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA901}}</ref>
Henry Neville Hutchinson was the eldest son of Thomas Neville Hutchinson, an Anglican clergyman and amateur naturalist.<ref>{{cite magazine|title=Obit. Canon Thomas Neville Hutchinson|magazine=Wiltshire Archæology and Natural History Magazine|volume=XXX |issue= XCI (pages 169–290)|page=275|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=I68UAAAAYAAJ&pg=RA1-PA275}}</ref> H. N. Hutchinson was educated at [[Rugby School]] and [[St John's College, Cambridge]], where he earned a bachelor's degree in 1878.<ref>{{cite book|editor=Holland, Arthur William|chapter=Hutchinson, Henry Neville|title=Oxford and Cambridge Yearbook. Part II. Cambridge|page=304|year=1904|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8ckCAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA330}}</ref> In 1879–1880 he was a student-master at [[Clifton College]]. In 1884 he was curate to St Saviour's, Redland Park, Bristol. In 1886–1887 he was private tutor to the sons of [[Albert Edmund Parker, 3rd Earl of Morley|the Earl of Morley]]. In 1891 he began literary work in London. He was an amateur naturalist and photographer, whose collection of photographs was exhibited at The Anthropological Institute of Great Britain and Ireland where he encouraged members to collect quality photographs for ethnological purposes.<ref>{{cite journal |date=1899 |title=Ordinary Meeting. December 6th, 1898 |url=https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=inu.30000098348711;view=1up;seq=321 |journal=The Journal of the Anthropological Institute of Great Britain and Ireland |volume=28 |pages=249 |location=London |publisher=Trübner & Co. |access-date=5 Jan 2017 }}</ref> He married in 1902.<ref name=Who/>
==Works== *[http://catalog.hathitrust.org/Record/007157294 ''Autobiography of the Earth''] (1890) *[http://catalog.hathitrust.org/Record/001273045 ''The Story of the Hills''] (1891) *[http://catalog.hathitrust.org/Record/000371826 ''Extinct Monsters''] (1892)<ref>{{cite book|author=LIghtman, Bernard|chapter=''Extinct Monsters''|title=Victorian Popularizers of Science|page=453|year=2007|publisher=University of Chicago Press|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ady3NSvPi_8C&pg=PA453}}</ref> *[http://catalog.hathitrust.org/Record/001994210 ''Creatures of Other Days''] (1894)<ref name="Creatures">{{cite book|author=LIghtman, Bernard|chapter=''Creatures of Other Days'' and ''Prehistoric Man and Beast''|title=Victorian Popularizers of Science|page=452|year=2007|publisher=University of Chicago Press|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ady3NSvPi_8C&pg=PA452}}</ref> *[http://catalog.hathitrust.org/Record/007129206 ''Prehistoric Man and Beast''] (1896)<ref name=Creatures/> *[http://catalog.hathitrust.org/Record/001879895 ''Descriptive Lecture on Pre-historic Man in Britain and Europe''] (1896) *''Marriage Customs in Many Lands'' (1897) *''Primæval Scenes'' (1899) *[https://books.google.com/books?id=Sv1PAAAAYAAJ&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_ge_summary_r&cad=0#v=onepage&q&f=false ''The living races of mankind: a popular illustrated account of the customs, habits, pursuits, feasts and ceremonies of the races of mankind throughout the world''] (1900) (with [[John Walter Gregory]] and [[Richard Lydekker]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=v-01AQAAMAAJ&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_ge_summary_r&cad=0#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=The Living Races of Mankind: A Popular Illustrated Account of the Customs, Habits, Pursuits, Feasts and Ceremonies of the Races of Mankind Throughout the World|first=Henry Neville|last=Hutchison|date=1 January 1902|publisher=Appleton|via=Google Books}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=xMY9AAAAMAAJ&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_ge_summary_r&cad=0#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=The Standard Library of Natural History: Embracing Living Animals of Thw World and Living Races If Mankind|first=Charles John|last=Cornish|date=1 January 1908|publisher=University society, Incorporated|via=Google Books}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=n5M9AQAAMAAJ&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_ge_summary_r&cad=0#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=The Standard Library of Natural History: Living races of mankind: v. 4. Oceania|date=1 January 1909|publisher=University Society, Incorporated|via=Google Books}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=lJA9AQAAMAAJ&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_ge_summary_r&cad=0#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=The people's natural history: embracing Living animals of the world and Living races of mankind|date=1 January 1905|publisher=University society|via=Google Books}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://archive.org/details/livingracesofman01hutcuoft|title=Living races of mankind : a popular illustrated account of the customs, habits, pursuits, feasts, and ceremonies of the races of mankind throughout the world|first=H. N. (Henry Neville)|last=Hutchinson|date=1 January 1902|publisher=London : Hutchinson|via=Internet Archive}}</ref> *[https://books.google.com/books?id=DDj6LRKRH9IC&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_ge_summary_r&cad=0#v=onepage&q&f=false ''The Living Races of Mankind''] By Richard Lydekker, Henry Neville Hutchinson, [[John Walter Gregory]] (1985) Mittal Publications [https://books.google.com/books?id=mSjYrlOYIfYC&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_ge_summary_r&cad=0#v=onepage&q&f=false Volume 2]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=v-01AQAAMAAJ&pg=PP13&dq=&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0CCgQ6AEwAGoVChMI48GPxL_nxwIVBWw-Ch3wEQDz#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=The Living Races of Mankind: A Popular Illustrated Account of the Customs, Habits, Pursuits, Feasts and Ceremonies of the Races of Mankind Throughout the World|first=Henry Neville|last=Hutchison|date=1 January 1902|publisher=Appleton|via=Google Books}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=qwI9AAAAIAAJ&pg=PR30&dq=&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0CDsQ6AEwA2oVChMI48GPxL_nxwIVBWw-Ch3wEQDz#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=Ethnology|date=1 January 1896|publisher=CUP Archive|via=Google Books}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=DDj6LRKRH9IC&pg=PR3-IA1&dq=&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0CEAQ6AEwBGoVChMI48GPxL_nxwIVBWw-Ch3wEQDz#v=onepage&q=&f=false|title=The Living Races of Mankind|first=Richard Lydekker, Henry Neville Hutchinson, John Walter|last=Gregory|publisher=Mittal Publications|via=Google Books}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://archive.org/details/akvamcihan0001ah|title=Akvam-? cihan /|first1=1865-1913|last1=01 Ahmet Hilmi Şehbenderzade|first2=|last2=01 احمد حلمى شهبندر زاده، 1865-1913|date=1 January 1913|publisher=Kostantiniye : Matbaa-yı Hikmet|via=Internet Archive}}</ref> *''The Living Rulers of Mankind'' (1901)
