[[File:Bursera-microphylla-baja.jpg|thumb|300px|''[[Bursera microphylla]]'' near [[Todos Santos, Baja California Sur]].]] The '''San Lucan xeric scrub''' is a [[deserts and xeric shrublands|xeric shrubland]] [[ecoregion]] of the southernmost [[Baja California Peninsula]], in [[Los Cabos Municipality]] and eastern [[La Paz Municipality, Baja California Sur|La Paz Municipality]] of southern [[Baja California Sur]] state, [[Mexico]].
==Setting== The San Lucan xeric scrub covers an area of {{convert|3,900|km2|sqmi|sp=us}}. It extends from sea level at the coasts up to {{convert|250|m|ft}} elevation in the [[Sierra de la Laguna]], where the [[Sierra de la Laguna dry forests]] ecoregion begins. Above that to the range's summits is the [[Sierra de la Laguna pine-oak forests]] ecoregion.
[[File:San Lucan Xeric Scrub map.svg|thumb|300px|left|Map of San Lucan xeric scrub ecoregion in [[Baja California Sur]] state.]] ==See also== *{{C|Flora of Baja California Sur}}
