{{about|the journal on [[energy economics]] published by the International Association for Energy Economics|the journal on energy in relation to technology management and policy|Energies (journal)}} {{infobox journal | title = The Energy Journal | cover = | discipline = [[Energy economics]] | editor = Adonis Yatchew | abbreviation = Energy J. | publisher = [[International Association for Energy Economics]] | country = | frequency = Quarterly | history = 1980-present | impact = 1.772 | impact-year = 2014 | openaccess = [[Hybrid open access journal|Hybrid]] | website = http://www.iaee.org/en/publications/scope.aspx | link1 = http://www.iaee.org/en/publications/journal.aspx | link1-name = Online access | link2 = http://www.iaee.org/en/publications/ejindex.aspx | link2-name = Online archive | ISSN = 0195-6574 | eISSN = 1944-9089 | JSTOR = 01956574 | OCLC = 563150979 | LCCN = 82641077 }} '''''The Energy Journal''''' is a quarterly [[peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] published by the [[International Association for Energy Economics]] and covering issues related to [[energy economics]]. It was established in 1980 and the [[editor-in-chief]] is Adonis Yatchew ([[University of Toronto]]).
==Impact and reception== According to the ''[[Journal Citation Reports]]'', the journal has a 2014 [[impact factor]] of 1.772, ranking it 23rd out of 88 journals in the category "Energy & Fuels".<ref name=WoS>{{cite book |year=2015 |chapter=Journals Ranked by Impact: Energy & Fuels |title=2014 [[Journal Citation Reports]] |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |edition=Science |series=[[Web of Science]]}}</ref>
